message.content:
We start by calculating the two requested ratios using the provided financial statement numbers.

Step 1: Gross Profit Margin
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 1,075,241.17  
  Total Revenue = 5,755,241.17
• Calculation:
  = (1,075,241.17 / 5,755,241.17) × 100%  
  ≈ 0.1868 × 100%  
  ≈ 18.68%

Step 2: Cash Flow to Debt Ratio
• This ratio is calculated as (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities).
• From the cash flow statement:
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -7,724,112.71
• From the balance sheet (using end amounts for current liabilities):
  Accounts Payable = 450,000.00  
  Taxes Payable = 287,762.05  
  Total Current Liabilities = 450,000.00 + 287,762.05 = 737,762.05
• Calculation:
  = -7,724,112.71 / 737,762.05  
  ≈ -10.47

Thus, the results are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "18.68%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-10.47"
  }
}
